      {
        "id": 5,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 6,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Rising Action - Crisis 3",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Middle of Part 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The fallout from Crisis 2 may not be as severe as the fallout from the first, but things continue to worsen for the Protagonist as they are thrust into another Crisis. Troubles continue to compound."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Continue to make things worse for the Protagonist while raising the stakes and the tension – for example, this could be a difficult state resulting from the fallout of the previous Crisis (e.g. being embarrassed, having to apologize publicly, losing rights or privileges, or other uncomfortable situations)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Include some falling action, lessons learned, character growth, and perhaps include a glimmer of hope."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Keep the subplot(s) in mind and how it continues to interact with the Main Plot and develop the character arc."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Hearing the commotion, the human runs into the room and grabs the dog to lock it away. The squirrel is given a moment to pause before it tries to head back to the peanuts and the back door. En route, the human comes by and gives chase to the squirrel. Frightened, it runs into another section of the house but away from the danger of the dog."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Part 1 makes up approximately the first 65% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Crisis 3 should occur around approximately the 30% mark of the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
