      {
        "id": 3,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 4,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Falling Action",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Part 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Falling Action wraps up the remaining storylines, loose ends, and character arcs of all main characters. The fallout from the Climax creates a transformation and change of perspective for the Protagonist, for better or worse. The end of the Falling Action brings about the Resolution, which shows how the Protagonist now interacts in their Ordinary World."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Wrap up any remaining storylines and conflicts."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Demonstrate if / how the Protagonist has transformed and what they have learned."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Show the Protagonist back in their Ordinary World having transformed (or not) and succeeded (or failed) at their task."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The squirrel plays dead as they are chased into the kitchen. Thinking its prey is dead, the cat drops it and dodges the human. Now, the squirrel makes a break for it and runs out the back door. The human follows after it, grabs a handful of peanuts and throws them on the ground outside. The human calls out, \"I don't mind feeding you out here, but stay out of my house. It is too dangerous, and you don't belong there.\" Then closes the door. The squirrel gathers the nuts and brings them back to its hungry family in the nest."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Part 3 makes up approximately the final 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Falling Action should occur at approximately the 75% mark of the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
