      {
        "id": 2,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 3,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Climax",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Part 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Protagonist has made it past the conflicts and complications of the Rising Action, yet now faces a complication that cannot be easily overcome. To succeed, the Protagonist must use what they have learned during the previous crises. If they are able to grow and learn, they will be successful; if they chose to remain mired in their old ways, they will fail or remain stagnant."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Set the Protagonist against a difficult situation that cannot be easily remedied."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Decide if the Protagonist learns from past mistakes or slides back to old ways."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Consider how the Climax will turn the rest of the story and impact the Protagonist's character arc."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Weigh the above points against any existing subplot(s) – this beat of the story has a pivotal impact on the Protagonist's transformations."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Seeing the cat ready to pounce, the squirrel has to decide whether to keep running, change course, or stop and turn back. The cat pounces and grabs the squirrel by the back of the neck. The human runs into the room and gives chase to the cat before it can harm the squirrel."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Part 2 makes up approximately 10% of the story from 65% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Climax should occur at approximately the 60% - 65% mark of the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
