        "title": "Rising Action - Crisis 1",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Part 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The story begins in the middle of a Crisis, with several more to come and little to no narrative exposition to start. Typically, Rising Action has three or 4 crises but can contain more if the narrative calls for it. Each Crisis acts as a plot point, working to raise the tension and stakes and offer exposition, backstory, and learning lessons for the Protagonist."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduce the Protagonist as they are dealing with a Crisis."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Hint at the Protagonist's internal and external goals and begin setting up their character arcs."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Include context and some backstory."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Any subplot(s) must be interwoven throughout the story, but during the Rising Action, be sure to include the Protagonist's backstory and other elements that impact their character arc. "
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A squirrel is inside a kitchen trying to get to a bag of peanuts. A human enters the room, sees the squirrel, and attempts to chase it out of the house, creating tension and drama as the squirrel escapes. The squirrel makes it outside and gets back to its nest and family, but they are still hungry. The squirrel begins working on another plan."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
